She's decided it's gonna be a boy.

24:35.760 --> 24:36.920
Course it's a boy,

24:36.920 --> 24:39.040
giving us all this trouble
getting pregnant.

24:41.520 --> 24:42.840
Guys, just take a seat for me.

24:42.840 --> 24:45.000
That's never a good sign, is it?

24:45.000 --> 24:47.640
Something the matter?
Just take a seat for me.

24:49.800 --> 24:51.840
MS HOUGHTON: Right, next customer!

24:54.680 --> 24:55.760
Um...

24:57.080 --> 24:59.600
..now, I can't find a heartbeat,

24:59.600 --> 25:03.200
which means that your baby
is no longer alive.

25:03.200 --> 25:05.280
Um, your options are to wait,

25:05.280 --> 25:07.640
er, see if the body passes it
naturally,

25:07.640 --> 25:11.320
we can give you some medicines
to speed things along or, er,

25:11.320 --> 25:14.360
we can book you in for an operation.
Do you understand?

25:16.280 --> 25:19.120
Er, could...could this be
a mistake?

25:19.120 --> 25:21.360
No, I'm afraid it's unmistakable.

25:21.360 --> 25:22.880
SHE SOBS UNCONTROLLABLY
I can show you

25:22.880 --> 25:24.160
the heart on the scanner

25:24.160 --> 25:26.080
if you like, but it's not moving.

25:26.080 --> 25:29.120
Um, in terms of which option
you'd like to go ahead with...

25:29.120 --> 25:31.200
SHE SOBS My baby.

25:31.200 --> 25:33.480
Well, it might be easier
not to think of it as a baby,

25:33.480 --> 25:34.960
it's just a bunch of cells.

25:36.200 --> 25:37.560
A bunch of cells?

25:39.600 --> 25:41.120
No.

25:41.120 --> 25:42.560
Sorry.

25:44.040 --> 25:46.800
Sorry, erm, that...
No, that's...that's...

25:46.800 --> 25:48.600
That's not what I meant,
that wasn't...

25:48.600 --> 25:50.880
No, we need to talk to
another doctor now!

25:54.560 --> 25:56.440
MS HOUGHTON:
Look, you're gonna get home

25:56.440 --> 25:58.480
and this afternoon's
just gonna be a big blur.

25:58.480 --> 26:00.920
All right?
So, here, take this leaflet.

26:00.920 --> 26:03.200
Right? It goes through everything
I've said.

26:03.200 --> 26:04.520
It's really good, actually.

26:04.520 --> 26:07.360
I mean, I wrote it,
so I would say it's good.

26:08.520 --> 26:10.200
Thanks so much, Doctor.

26:10.200 --> 26:13.880
Listen, there's no hurry
to make a decision, OK?

26:13.880 --> 26:16.320
You just get in touch whenever

26:16.320 --> 26:19.360
and we'll book you in
for the tablets or the operation.

26:19.360 --> 26:21.040
Actually, you know what?

26:24.160 --> 26:25.920
This is my mobile number.

26:25.920 --> 26:28.120
Give me a call directly
and I'll sort it.

26:29.720 --> 26:31.160
Thank you, Doctor.  Thanks again.

26:32.840 --> 26:36.400
And I am really sorry again
for what she said earlier.

26:36.400 --> 26:39.920
She's very junior,
but that falls absolutely miles

26:39.920 --> 26:42.520
short of what I expect
from my doctors.

26:42.520 --> 26:44.160
I'm really disappointed in her.

26:47.080 --> 26:48.160
Thank you.

26:51.000 --> 26:52.240
OK.

27:04.000 --> 27:05.560
It's all sorted.

27:05.560 --> 27:08.320
These things happen, mate.
Don't stress it.  OK.

27:13.040 --> 27:14.360
PAGER BEEPS

27:14.360 --> 27:17.840
# Kept thinking I could never
live without you

27:17.840 --> 27:19.240
# By my side... #

27:20.400 --> 27:21.680
Oh, sorry.

27:25.560 --> 27:27.200
Thank you so much for seeing her.

27:27.200 --> 27:30.400
I didn't. She discharged herself
half an hour after you left.

27:30.400 --> 27:33.000
Shit. What do we do now?

27:34.480 --> 27:35.520
Nothing.

27:38.000 --> 27:39.840
PAGER BEEPS

27:43.520 --> 27:44.960
MUFFLED CHATTER

27:53.000 --> 27:54.280
CHATTER STOPS

27:57.040 --> 27:58.960
SCREAMING
TROLLEY CLATTERS

27:58.960 --> 28:00.080
CHATTER RESUMES

28:02.160 --> 28:03.640
PAGER BEEPS

28:05.800 --> 28:07.160
What now?

28:07.160 --> 28:08.560
Adam, thank God you're here.

28:08.560 --> 28:10.840
There's three patients
I need you to see.

28:10.840 --> 28:13.000
Which one's the most urgent?
Oh, God.

28:13.000 --> 28:15.400
ECHOES:  Thank God you're here.
D'you want your consultant in?

28:15.400 --> 28:16.960
It was you.

28:16.960 --> 28:18.280
It was me?

28:18.280 --> 28:20.680
You complained.  Adam, are you OK?

28:20.680 --> 28:22.920
Let's get you into a chair,
shall we?

28:29.280 --> 28:30.760
Can you move your arm?

28:31.800 --> 28:33.560
I think you've had a stroke.

28:33.560 --> 28:34.960
I haven't had a stroke. I'm fine.

28:37.920 --> 28:39.800
I just... I didn't eat my breakfast.

28:39.800 --> 28:42.080
I'll make you a wee slice
of toast, love.

28:47.000 --> 28:48.320
Keep an eye on him.

28:48.320 --> 28:50.840
I think he's had a wee stroke.

29:17.000 --> 29:18.680
Oh, hi. HE CLEARS THROAT

29:18.680 --> 29:20.120
You can go straight through.

29:20.120 --> 29:21.320
What time do you finish?

29:22.520 --> 29:23.960
Oh, er, right.

29:23.960 --> 29:26.000
Er, in about an hour.

29:26.000 --> 29:27.800
OK, I will see you
at the Working Men's Club

29:27.800 --> 29:29.320
on Pollard Road for seven.

29:29.320 --> 29:31.400
You having a big pre-exams party,
or...?

29:32.760 --> 29:34.120
Is that a no?

29:34.120 --> 29:37.200
No. It's a yes, obviously.

29:43.360 --> 29:45.240
All right?  One of those days.

29:45.240 --> 29:47.440
Aren't they all? Good luck tomorrow.

29:47.440 --> 29:49.080
You'll nail it.

29:49.080 --> 29:51.640
You can wish me luck properly
at the party.

29:51.640 --> 29:53.440
Are you coming?

29:53.440 --> 29:54.760
Yeah, why not?

29:58.280 --> 30:01.360
Well, I'm not paying for your resits
if they breathalyse you.

30:03.880 --> 30:05.680
Looks like there are fewer tubes.

30:07.040 --> 30:08.880
That's got to be a good thing,
right?

30:08.880 --> 30:10.680
Unless one's fallen out -
that would be...

30:12.680 --> 30:14.080
..that would be a bad thing.

30:15.840 --> 30:17.240
Anyway, hopefully, you'll...

30:19.280 --> 30:21.480
..you'll be out of here
before too long.

30:23.720 --> 30:26.600
As it turns out, I'll probably
beat you out of here...

30:27.920 --> 30:29.120
..because some total...

30:30.920 --> 30:32.080
..colleague...

30:33.600 --> 30:35.240
..is trying to get me struck off.

30:36.400 --> 30:38.760
I give my life to this shithole
and this is...

30:40.520 --> 30:41.560
HE SIGHS

30:45.400 --> 30:47.240
You don't think I deserve it,
do you?

30:51.960 --> 30:55.640
I'm sorry Emma can't make it
tonight, she just...

30:55.640 --> 30:57.200
Didn't wanna come?

30:57.200 --> 30:59.280
No, it's not that.

30:59.280 --> 31:01.920
Well, yeah, it is that, slightly.

31:01.920 --> 31:03.720
So, have you sorted a date, then?

31:03.720 --> 31:06.000
